// `zzz_undefined` is not declared anywhere. The bare-instruction inline path
// retargets the body's spans to the call site without running substitution,
// so before the fix `Expr::IdentSpanned` retained its byte offsets from this
// source — the resulting diagnostic was anchored at the *byte offset in the
// caller's source* corresponding to those offsets, which lands on unrelated
// code. After the fix the retargeting strips those offsets, anchoring the
// diagnostic at the call site instead.

inline broken {
    lda zzz_undefined
}
